  The Krugersdorp SAPS has launched a campaign called Divine Intervention, lead by Chaplain Apostolic Lieutenant Colonel Maluleke. The Krugersdorp SAPS was prayed for by pastors from Mogale city and Merafong. SAPS spokesman, Captain Raymond Sebonyane said all areas of policing by Krugersdorp SAPS were prayed for, they also motivated the members. “When it comes to the work that we do, a need for prayers and some motivation is very important,” he said. The Station Commander of Krugersdorp SAPS Brigadier Mashao and management appreciated the support from all pastors and members for making this day a success. 